<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1436,1146,1340]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1188,1214]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body fusiform; scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[719,743,1188,1213]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">sc</emphasis>
) and tubercles on rear shield margin, directed posteriorly; coxae I and coxae II each with 3 setae; empodium entire; opisthosoma with annuli differentiated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1436,1146,1340]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
This genus consists of 27 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[616,846,1272,1298]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[716,768,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Ten of these have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
